from selenium import webdriver
from selenium.webdriver.chrome.service import Service
from webdriver_manager.chrome import ChromeDriverManager
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import re
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd

url = "https://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/stats/index.html?class=11;page=1;template=results;type=batting"

driver = webdriver.Chrome(service=Service(ChromeDriverManager().install()))

Player = []
Span = []
Matches = []
Innings = []
Runs = []
Ave= []
hs=[]
hundreds = []
fifties = []


for page in range(1, 10):  
    url = f"https://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/stats/index.html?class=11;page={page};template=results;type=batting"
    driver.get(url)
    print(url)

    soup = BeautifulSoup(driver.page_source, "html.parser")
    rows = soup.find_all('tr', class_='data1')

    for row in rows:
        cols = row.find_all('td')
        if len(cols) > 0:
            Player.append(cols[0].text.strip())
            Span.append(cols[1].text.strip())
            Matches.append(cols[2].text.strip())
            Innings.append(cols[3].text.strip())
            Runs.append(cols[5].text.strip())
            hs.append(cols[6].text.strip())
            Ave.append(cols[7].text.strip())
            hundreds.append(cols[8].text.strip())
            fifties.append(cols[9].text.strip())

Business Promblem

ESPN Cricinfo provides vast cricket statistics used by selectors, analysts, broadcasters, fantasy platforms, and fans. However, raw statistical tables alone do not easily reveal player consistency, performance trends, or relationships between key batting metrics.

Decision-makers need data-driven insights to:

Compare players objectively

Identify consistent and high-impact batters

Understand how career longevity affects performance

Analyze performance across different eras

Promblem Statements

Cricket analytics platforms such as ESPN Cricinfo provide extensive historical batting data; however, the data is presented in raw tabular form, making it difficult to derive meaningful insights directly. There is a need to analyze and visualize this data to understand player performance, consistency, and trends over time. This project aims to apply exploratory data analysis and statistical techniques to identify key performance indicators and relationships among batting metrics.

OBJECTIVES OF THE ANALYSIS

  1. Identify top-performing batters based on runs, averages, centuries, and half-centuries.

  2. Analyze the relationship between career length (matches) and performance.

  3. Compare batting performance across different eras.

  4. Determine whether high run scorers are also more consistent.

  5. Validate insights using statistical hypothesis testing.

  6. Present insights using univariate, bivariate, and multivariate visualizations.

print("P-value:", p_value)

Effect of Runs & Matches on Batting Average

In[17]:
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.formula.api import ols

df['Runs_Group'] = pd.qcut(df['Runs'], q=2, labels=['Low Runs', 'High Runs'])
df['Matches_Group'] = pd.qcut(df['Matches'], q=2, labels=['Low Matches', 'High Matches'])

model = ols(
    'Average ~ C(Runs_Group) + C(Matches_Group) + C(Runs_Group):C(Matches_Group)',
    data=df
).fit()

anova_table = sm.stats.anova_lm(model, typ=2)
print(anova_table)

Runs Group vs 100s Group

In[18]:
from scipy.stats import chi2_contingency
import pandas as pd

df['Runs_Group'] = pd.cut(df['Runs'], bins=2, labels=['Low Runs', 'High Runs'])
df['Hundreds_Group'] = pd.cut(df['100s'], bins=2, labels=['Low 100s', 'High 100s'])

contingency = pd.crosstab(df['Runs_Group'], df['Hundreds_Group'])
print(contingency)

chi2, p_value, dof, expected = chi2_contingency(contingency)

print("Chi-square:", chi2)
print("P-value:", p_value)
